@name Developer Guide: Directives: Creating Angular Directives
@description

The following code snippet shows how to define a custom directive. You define a new directive by
extending the {@link compiler angular HTML compiler}. The code snippet below is a simplified
definition of the built-in {@link api/angular.directive.ng:bind ng:bind} directive:

<pre>
angular.directive('ng:bind', function(expression, compiledElement) {
var compiler = this;
return function(linkElement) {
var currentScope = this;
currentScope.$watch(expression, function(value) {
  linkElement.text(value);
});
};
});
</pre>


